1161C 101st Legislative Session 1161
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1161
AMENDME NT 1161C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Kull
1 An Act to amend provisions related to changing rooms, sleeping quarters, and
2 restrooms.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 20-13-58 be AMENDED:
5 20-13-58. Terms used in §§ 20-13-58 to 20-13-63, inclusive, mean:
6 (1) "Changing room," a room or area in which an individual may be in a state of undress in
7 the presence of others, including a multi-occupancy locker room or shower room, which is
8 open to the public;
9 (2) "Female," an individual who naturally has, had, will have, or would have had, but for a
10 congenital anomaly or intentional or unintentional disruption, the reproductive system that
11 produces, transports, and utilizes eggs for fertilization;
12 (3) "Male," an individual who naturally has, had, will have, or would have had, but for a
13 congenital anomaly or intentional or unintentional disruption, the reproductive system that
14 produces, transports, and utilizes sperm for fertilization;
15 (4) "Restroom," a room that includes at least one toilet or urinal;
16 (5) "Sleeping quarters," a room that contains a bed and in which more than one individual is
17 housed overnight;
18 (6) "Sex," an individual's biological sex, either male or female; and
19 (7) "Unisex or family room," a changing room or restroom that:
20 (a) Is intended for use by a single occupant, a single occupant and the occupant's caregiver,
21 or members of the same family;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1161C 2 1161
1 (b) Is enclosed by means of floor-to-ceiling walls; and
2 (c) Is accessible by means of a full door, with a secure lock that prevents entry by another
3 individual while the room is in use.
4 Section 1. That § 20-13-59 be AMENDED:
5 20-13-59. Except as otherwise provided in this section and §§ 13-32-22 and 13-
6 32-23, the state or a political subdivision of this state must designate, as being for the
7 exclusive use of females or males, any multi-occupancy changing room, multi-occupancy
8 restroom, or sleeping quarters in:
9 (1) A building or facility owned by the state or by a political subdivision of this state;
10 or
11 (2) A space leased to or occupied by the state or by a political subdivision of this state.
12 This section does not apply to any room used exclusively by firefighters, law
13 enforcement personnel, or musical and theatrical entertainers, or to any room used
14 entered for a governmental regulatory purpose or law enforcement personnel acting in an
15 official capacity.
16 Section 2. That § 20-13-61 be AMENDED:
17 20-13-61. The prohibitions set forth in § 20-13-60 do not apply to:
18 (1) An individual who accompanies a child under the age of ten, if the individual is the
19 child's parent or lawful chaperone;
20 (2) An individual who accompanies another individual requiring assistance because of
21 age or a disability;
22 (3) A law enforcement officer, fire official, firefighter, or other state or county
23 employee of the state or a political subdivision who is acting in an official capacity;
24 (4) An individual providing emergency medical assistance;
25 (5) An individual providing custodial, maintenance, or inspection services, provided the
26 changing room or restroom is unoccupied; or
27 (6) An individual providing services or rendering aid:
28 (a) During a natural disaster or declared emergency; or
29 (b) When necessary to maintain order and safety.; or
30 (7) Firefighters, individuals who are actively engaged in musical, theatrical, or
31 similar performances, or law enforcement personnel, when using changing
